      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Not less than 500 Indians, the\nlargest aggregation of original red\nmed ever assembled in Spokane\nwill make up the big Indian village\nat the approaching Spokane Inter\nstate Fair, says Sam Cone, former\nspecial government Indian agent\nwho has just returned from an ex'\ntended trip through the Flathead\nreservation in Montana.\n\n\nOn all the reservations in the In\nland Empire, particularly on the\nNez Perce reserve. nightly pow\nvows are being held IN preparation\nfor the Battle of the Clearwater.\nwhich is to be fought nightly at the\nfair. The old bucks put in theil\nspare time beside the evening camp\nfire telling the rising generation\nabout frontier fights. In turn the\nyoung braves and even the dusky\nyoungsters have caught the spirit\nAgain the tom-tom resounds, the\nwar cry awakes the echoes in the\nforest shades, and again the wal\ndance is on."
    }
